column4: A lot of pre-diabetics would have borderline HbA1C. Right on the cusp. Some normal, some marginally abnormal. They would be followed annually by serial HbA1C.
For #99 and #100 we would NOT typically test for HbA1C unless the abnormal glucose has persisted for a few months and or the patient presents with very high glucose and or a complication.
Not specific for Salmonella. CRP is elevated in all infections ( inflammatory states)
